        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Singapore takes on hackers</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/unc3886-chinese-cyber-espionage-group-defense-tech-telecom.jpg" alt="UNC3886 is identified as a top Chinese cyber espionage group, known for targeting the defense, technology, and telecommunications industries" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>UNC3886 is identified as a top Chinese cyber espionage group, known for targeting the defense, technology, and telecommunications industries. Credits: Lianhe Zaobao</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> Singapore asserted that its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-critical-infrastructure-was-attacked" target="_blank">critical infrastructure was attacked</a> by a Chinese-affiliated hacking group known as UNC3886. They quickly escalated the response by involving the armed forces and the defense ministry to dismantle the attackers' networks. Meanwhile, the Chinese embassy denied the involvement and reiterated how China is also a victim of cyberattacks.  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The why:</strong> Analysts suggest that Singapore’s close ties with the US and Taiwan have made the island nation a target. They also view the involvement of the Singaporean Armed Forces as a protective measure rather than an offensive move. Singapore has been subjected to multiple cyberattacks, including the Singtel and SingHealth breaches, due to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-vulnerabilities-in-the-cloud-infrastructure" target="_blank">vulnerabilities in the cloud infrastructure</a>.   
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>The big picture:</strong> Cyberattacks by these Chinese-affiliated groups have increased by over 150% year-on-year in 2024, and the US was the most targeted. A recent example is the attack by the Storm-2603 group, which infiltrated <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-the-sharepoint-system" target="_blank">the SharePoint system</a>. 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
