          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500"> 
          Thai and Cambodian clash</h2>
        </mj-text> 
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>
            Summary: Thailand and Cambodia are engaged in deadly clashes over a disputed border temple.</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> Armed clashes between <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-thai-and-cambodian-troops" target="_blank">Thai and Cambodian troops</a> at their disputed border have killed at least 14 people in Thailand and one in Cambodia. This escalation happened hours after the diplomatic efforts were downgraded over a land mine blast that injured a Thai soldier. Both countries have closed their border, imposed a ban on imports, and boycotted international internet links. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The why:</strong> The 1907 map drawn under French colonial rule provides Cambodia with territorial assertions along the border, including the 1,000-year-old <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-preah-vihear-temple" target="_blank">Preah Vihear temple</a>. Although the International Court of Justice awarded sovereignty over the temple area to Cambodia in 1963 and reaffirmed this in the 2013 hearing, Thailand disputes the accuracy of the map. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           <strong>On the ground:</strong> This latest escalation occurs during a period of political instability in both countries. Thailand’s PM was suspended over violations in handling the border dispute. Her <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-disrespectful-comments" target="_blank">disrespectful comments</a> about the Cambodian PM were leaked, leading to protests. The PM has apologized and argued her comments were a negotiating tactic.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section> 

