            "> Worldwide </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/foreign-relations-map-asia-europe-influence.jpg" alt="Illustration of geopolitical influence showing international flags connected to a central Asian region on a world map" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              padding-top: 0px;
              padding-bottom: 6px;
            ">
            <strong>🇨🇳 China - Drone aid to Russia.</strong> China is secretly sending drone engines to Russia, disguising them as “cooling units.” This helps Moscow increase Garpiya-A1 drone production, even with Western sanctions. These findings appeared just before an EU-China summit, heightening concerns about Beijing’s support for Russia’s war (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-worldwide-9-weapons-in-disguise" target="_blank">weapons in disguise</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
          <strong>🇵🇸 Palestine - Hamas disappoints mediators.</strong> Hamas rejected the ceasefire and hostage agreement as they introduced renewed demands that Qatar and Egypt find unacceptable. Israel has not been officially notified, but has been briefed and is still in talks. The main issues are troop withdrawal distances and prisoner releases. Mediators want Hamas to change its response to keep negotiations going (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-worldwide-10-still-not-there" target="_blank">still not there</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
          <strong>🇰🇷 South Korea - Fertile May.</strong> In May 2025, South Korea experienced a 3.8% rise in births. A total of 20,309 babies were born, marking the largest May increase in 14 years. This marks the 11th consecutive month of year-on-year growth. Officials say more marriages and a larger group of women in their early 30s are behind the rise. Still, deaths outnumber births, which continues the country’s natural population decline (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-worldwide-11-signs-of-improvement" target="_blank">signs of improvement</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
          <strong>🇹🇷 Turkey - Closer to Eurofighter jets</strong>. Turkey and the UK signed a Memorandum of Understanding on July 23 to advance Ankara’s potential $5.6B trade of up to 40 Eurofighter Typhoon jets. Germany has reportedly cleared the export. The agreement strengthens NATO airpower and signals Turkey’s push to modernize its air force alongside parallel F-16 talks and domestic fighter programs (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-worldwide-12-turkish-aviation-glow-up" target="_blank">Turkish aviation glow up</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
           <strong>🇫🇷 France - To recognize Palestine</strong>. President Emmanuel Macron announced that France will recognize Palestine as a state. He cited the need to end the Gaza war and reduce humanitarian suffering. This move will be formalized at the UN in September. Macron called it a step toward peace. Israel condemned the decision, but Palestinians and European allies welcomed it (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jul-25-worldwide-13-western-recognition" target="_blank">Western recognition</a>). 
          </p>
        </mj-text>
